  "title": "Project Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Role</strong></p>\n<p>The Project Coordinator will provide administrative and coordination support for the Project Management Office and support the Project Managers in their delivery of projects. The ideal candidate is a multi-tasker skilled in communications (both internally and externally) and a master in coordination and scheduling works. The Project Coordinator is responsible for scheduling meetings, coordinating resources, projects profit and loss calculation, project reports, managing Project Warehouse inventory, and tracking expenses.</p>\n<p>We are looking for a teammate who is meticulous and pro-active. The Project Coordinator is expected to have good oral and written communication abilities and have a sound understanding of project management cycle. They should be organized, reliable and able to handle stressful situations.</p>\n<p><strong>The Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Prepare, or assist with the preparation of reporting and metrics associated with the successful implementation and execution of projects – Project Progress Reports, Inventory List, User Acceptance Test, etc.</p>\n<p>· Track and preparation of project claims and project billings</p>\n<p>· Track and update on respective project status to Manager</p>\n<p>· Track and recognize project costs</p>\n<p>· Participate in external meetings and assist with meeting minutes</p>\n<p>· Assist with scheduling and gathering necessary resources</p>\n<p>· Co-manage the Project Warehouse with the Managers</p>\n<p>· Sourcing and placing orders for cables/accessories/sub-contractors, etc.</p>\n<p>· Preparation and submission of scheduled reports every month-end to Management</p>\n<p>· Assisting the Manager with project hours and recognition</p>\n<p>· Assist with ISO 9001 / 45001 audits</p>\n<p>· Other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the Manager</p>\n<p><strong>The ideal candidate should possess the following;</strong></p>\n<p>· Diploma or Bachelors/Undergraduate degree in a related field such as business management, business administration, information technology, or computer science, or equivalent work experience</p>\n<p>· Prior experience as a project administrator or a related administrative role</p>\n<p>· Attention to detail</p>\n<p>· Excellent interpersonal and communication skills</p>\n<p>· Excellent organizational skills</p>\n<p>· Proficiency with Microsoft Office</p>\n<p>· Ability to effectively manage time and prioritize to meet deadlines</p>\n<p>· Self-starter who takes charge in absence of detailed instruction; effectively initiates solutions or discussions</p>\n<p>· Strong written and verbal English language skills</p>",
